The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Paes amp; Co. to play Brazil
                                                                                                                       7                                      Paes amp; Co. to play Brazil
                      
	New Delhi: India will compete at home against Brazil in the Davis Cup World Group play-off tie from September 17 to 19. After a long time, India will have home advantage as they have played all their ties outside the country recently.         
	Since India had played their last tie against Brazil in Sao Paulo in 1991, India have got a home tie this time round.         
	India had lost to Russia in March in the first round of the World Group to get to the play-offs while Brazil had whitewashed Uruguay 5-0 in the semi-finals of the America Zone group I competition to give themselves a chance to re-enter the World Group.         
	They last played in the World Group in 2003 while India played in the World Group after a long gap of 11 years. The head-to-head score between India and Brazil is tied at 1-1. The winning nation will advance to first round of the World Group while the losing country will compete in their respective Zone Group. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
